  <!-- Introducción de la lección (narrative) -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-leccion-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>In previous lessons, students learned what it means for two fractions to be equivalent. In this lesson, students continue to reason about and show equivalence visually, building on their work with fraction strips. They use shaded diagrams to help them generate equivalent fractions, including fractions greater than 1. The work here prepares students to use number lines to explain fraction equivalence later in the section.</p>
  </paragraphs>
  
  <!-- Preguntas de reflexión profesor -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="reflection-quest-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>Which students had opportunities to share their diagrams and thinking during whole-class discussion? How did you select these students?</p>
  </paragraphs>
</introduction>


